Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteDanglingPort(25.10)                            deleteDanglingPort(25.10)

Name
       deleteDanglingPort  - Deletes module ports that are disconnected on the
       outside

Syntax
       deleteDanglingPort

       [-help]

       [-ptn]

       Deletes module ports that are disconnected on the outside.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each deleteDanglingPort parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteDanglingPort

       -ptn   Evaluate for deletion only ports on partition boundaries.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
       Delete all dangling ports on all partitions

       deleteDanglingPort -ptn

